# Clean DDD SOLID Rules

## Purpose
These rules keep this project aligned with practical DDD + Clean Architecture + SOLID.

## Architecture Boundaries
- `domain` contains entities, value objects, domain events, and pure invariants.
- `application` contains use cases and ports only.
- `interfaces` contains delivery adapters (HTTP, messaging).
- `infrastructure` contains persistence/messaging implementations.
- `shared` contains cross-cutting concerns (config, logger, validator, httpx, resilience).

## Dependency Rule
- Dependency points inward.
- `domain` must not import framework packages.
- `application` depends on abstractions in `application/port`.
- `interfaces` and `infrastructure` can import `application` and `shared`.

## SOLID (Practical)
- SRP: handlers are thin; use cases orchestrate business flow.
- OCP: add new adapters by implementing ports.
- ISP: keep interfaces small and focused.
- DIP: use cases depend on ports, never concrete infra implementations.

## HTTP Rules
- Validate request body with validator tags.
- Return errors through centralized error handler (`code`, `type`, `message`, `request_id`).
- Keep transport DTOs in `internal/interfaces/http/<resource>/dto.go`.
- Mapping logic stays in `mapper.go`, not in handlers.

## Persistence Rules
- Use SQL migrations only (`golang-migrate`), no AutoMigrate in production.
- GORM models stay in `internal/infrastructure/persistence`.
- Repositories return sentinel errors (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrConflict`) mapped centrally.

## Messaging Rules
- Do not publish domain events directly inside use case transaction.
- Use outbox write inside transaction, then dispatch from consumer.
- Apply retry/backoff and circuit breaker in dispatcher.

## Security & Ops
- Protect API routes with API key auth + permission checks when enabled.
- Keep liveness/readiness and metrics endpoints available for operations.
- Log structured JSON for Loki-compatible pipelines.

## Team Workflow
- Follow commit convention from `.cursor/rules/commit-message-standard.mdc`.
- Follow security baseline from `.cursor/rules/security-owasp-top10.mdc`.
- Follow quality baseline from `.cursor/rules/code-quality-sonarqube.mdc`.
